cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper involves computer vision techniques such as 3D reconstruction and image rendering, which are commonly associated with the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper also deals with graphics and modeling, which are related to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. The use of neural networks for rerendering and semantic labeling suggests a focus on machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves the use of latent appearance vectors, which are commonly used in generative models, indicating a possible connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the creation of short videos suggests a focus on multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
